Best known as a beauty queen, Urvashi Rautela has managed to establish herself as a Bollywood star and delighted her fans all around the world. This stunningly beautiful model and actor has many sides to her like a multi-faceted jewel. Here are some little known Urvashi Rautela latest n unknown facts

1.) She was stripped off her Miss Universe India crown.

In 2012, she won the coveted Miss Universe India beauty pageant but had to return the crown when the judges found out that she was underage.

2.) She is the only two-time Miss Universe India in history.

Yes, Urvashi Rautela is a trailblazer with regards to so many things. One such notable fete that she has managed to pull is wearing the Miss Universe India crown twice. Having been stripped off the Crown the first time, she managed to win and retain it in 2015. No other woman has been able to achieve this yet.

3.) The secret to her stunning beauty.

In addition to proper nutrition and meditation, the gorgeous Urvashi strongly believes in physical fitness. Sh is professionally trained in five different dance forms including Bharatanatyam, Kathat, belly dancing, jazz and hip-hop. Most people probably remember her from Yo Yo Honey Singh’s Lovedose’ video album in which she starred in 2014.

Furthermore, she is a basketball player at the national level. Believe it or not, she has represented India in sporting events as well.

4.) She’s all beauty and brains.

Before joining modelling, Urvashi wanted to pursue engineering. She had successfully cleared her IIT (Indian Institutes of Technology) exams but later opted for the glamorous career in modelling.

5.) She’s beautiful both on the outside and in the inside as well.

Alongside her modelling and acting career, Urvashi Rautela is involved in running The Urvashi Rautela Foundation together with her family. Her foundation seeks to empower the underprivileged people in Indian society.

On the onset, I would like to make a confession. I am a ‘die hard’ Parineeti Chopra fan. Whether it be her great looks, her mind blowing dressing sense or her always congenial mood, she is, in all ways, adorable. However, many of us fans don’t know about the other half of Parineeti. This half likes playing with numbers and dreams of making a career out of singing!

1. Parineeti was an all India Topper in her 12th standard

Yes, you heard that right. She has repeatedly confessed in interviews that she was a very sincere student. In fact, she received an award for her achievement from none other than Pratibha Patil, the then President of India.

2. She has a – wait for it! – TRIPLE degree in business, economics and management from Manchester University

Parineeti always dreamed of being a successful Investment Banker. She says that numbers used to give her an adrenaline rush! To that end, she successfully pursued a triple degree from Manchester University.

3. A trained singer, she has a BA (Hons) in Music

As evident from her recently released track, she has a great voice. However, this voice hasn’t come out of no where. She has worked on it. Besides a BA (Hons) in Music, she has sung in many programs throughout her childhood.

4. She is a devoted humanitarian and active in charity work

Parineeti, along with a great brain and looks, seems to have a great heart too! She set a great example by taking to the ramp in the Indian Fashion Week organised by Wills Lifestyle to support the Shabana Azmi Mijwan welfare society. This welfare society helps in empowering the girl child.

After getting to know this side of Parineeti, I have really started to admire her as a person. No doubt, she is a true star!

………………………………………………………………………………….

Latest news about Parineeti Chopra

My favorite actress, Parineeti Chopra, has a great screen presence. She seems to turn heads wherever she goes. Here are few of the reasons she has been making headlines recently:

1. Fight with Shraddha Kapoor

Oops! Parineeti Chopra and Shraddha Kapoor are in bit of a tight situation. Both of them want to exclusively perform at the upcoming Justin Beiber concert in Mumbai to promote their respective films. While we really want Parineeti to sing, the jury is still out on who will get the spot!

2. ‘Maana Ki Hum Yaar Nahin’ was not auto tuned

In a twitter post, Parineeti Chopra has revealed that the song was not auto tuned at all. Recently, we have all seen great singers shunning bollywood playback songs as they feel that they are all auto tuned. Consequentially, they lack originality. But not Parineeti, her awesome voice is good enough. There is really no need for any other intervention!

3. Want to be a Producer

After Priyanka Chopra and Anushka Sharma, it is Parineeti Chopra’s turn. In a recently published interview, the actress has confessed that even she would like to be a producer someday. According to her, she has a business mindset which can be combined with a passion for film making to produce rich dividends. So, here’s wishing her a big all the best for her career as a producer.

Just as stars never lose their shine, Parineeti Chopra is here to stay. So, keep following our blog to more news about Parineeti Chopra. Thank you!

She has a quite successful career, as she worked with some of the greatest names of Indian movie scene. Since her debut in 2007. she had some significant roles for which she received good critics. She won screen award for movie called “Yeh Saali Zindagi” from 2011. Not only she’s a successful actress, but she is also a very good at singing which she showed through some of her roles like the one from the “London, Paris, New York” movie.

She is currently working on various projects and roles which look promising. Her latest movie was released in April 2017. called “Kaatru Veliyidai” in which she plays a doctor who’s falling into romantic relationship with Karthi. She is always present in Indian media and lots of stories are being written about her each month. In 2015. she posted a selfie on the Indian Independence Day, saluting with her left hand which insulted her fans. People said that it was a quite disrespectful act and that she doesn’t care about her country’s tradition at all.

In 2016, she was driving to a fashion show event in Noida but she wasn’t driving pretty well, because police caught her for driving her car on the wrong side of the road! We don’t know if she was drunk or just so excited about the show but she should have not let herself do something like this. Trisha Krishnan is an Indian actress acting majorly in South Indian film industries. She was born on May 3rd, 1983 at Tamil Nadu India. She is 5-feet and 6-inch in height. Rana, who is a southern superstar, however, denied the act claiming that someone hacked his account. From the previous secrets, the two are known for their on and off relationship and love affair. However, the duo denied saying that they were just “Thick friends.”

Trisha is a fashionista and takes pride in being the best dressed at every event. However, she doesn’t always have the right attire but still manages to wear a broad smile.

She got the Miss Madras title at the age of 16 and managed to reach the finals of the Miss India completion. She failed to get the last crown, but her fame had started to spread.

Rakul Preet Singh is an actress and model. She was born on 10th October 1990. Preet Singh plays roles in Telugu films though she has appeared in several Tamil, Kannada and Hindi films.

Life and unknown facts about Rakul Preet Singh.

Rakul started her modelling assignments while she was in college. While still modelling she made her first acting debut in the Kanadda film Gilli in 2009. In 2011, Rakul participated in Femina Miss India pageant where she was placed fifth and she also won five pageant titles that includes the �Miss India People’s Choice’.

She chose to be a full-time Telugu actress where she made a Telugu debut in Keratam. In the following year she made a Tamil debut in the film Thadaiyara Thakka. In the year 2014 she made her Bollywood debut in the film Yaariyan where her performance was well received. The film was directed by Divya Kumar.

Preet Singh played a role in a commercially successful Telugu films that include the Venkatadri Express produced in 2013, Current Theega in 2014 and Loukyam also in 2014. These movies promoted her career opening up opportunities to bigger projects in the film industry. She played roles in successful movies such Kick 2 in 2015, Bruce Lee also in2015, Nannaku Prematho, Sarrainodu and Dhruva in 2016. After the production of Venkatadri, she was nominated for the Best Actress at the 61st Filmware Awards South.

Rakul has played roles with well-known actors such as Sai Dharam Tej and Mahesh Babu. In September 2016, she signed for a Telugu film that was directed by Kaylan Krishna where she starred with Naga Chaitanya. Later in December 2016, she signed for her latest film Theeran Athikaram Ondru where she stars opposite Karthi.

After the production of several successful movies, she has been established as one of the leading actresses in Telugu Cinema.

Rakul is said to have opened a gym called F45 in Gachibowli Hyderabad. She lives in Hyderabad with her parents.
